An Act relative to fair worker representation on joint purchasing group committees.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Section 12 of chapter 32B of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2018 Official Edition,
2 is hereby amended by inserting at the end of paragraph 2 the following:- "Should a governmental
3 agency enter into a trust or joint purchase agreement, a board and steering committee shall be
4 established, including members of the appropriate public authorities, a minimum of one quarter
5 (25%) of the members shall come from labor representatives elected from a list of
6 representatives nominated by the collective bargaining units and a retiree from one of the
7 governmental units appointed by the Retired State, County, and Municipal Association of
8 Massachusetts. All members will be considered voting members.
